The paper deals with machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computer science (cs). The paper specifically focuses on a Chinese machine reading comprehension dataset, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of NLP related to Chinese language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of rule-based and neural methods, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of data augmentation and distractor plausibility, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.NE, in that order.
